title: Urban Waste Collection and Recycling Drop-Off Routing
desc_split:
A municipal waste management company operates trucks to collect household waste (linehaul) and pick up recyclables (backhaul) from designated bins across the city. Each truck (capacity: `<capacity>`) starts at the depot (`<loc_depot>`) and must visit `<num_customer>` locations (`<loc_customer>`), where each stop has either waste to collect (`<demand_linehaul>`) or recyclables to pick up (`<demand_backhaul>`). Mixed sequencing is allowed (e.g., a truck can alternate between waste and recycling stops). Routes must respect:  
- **Time windows** (`<time_windows>`): Bins are only accessible during specific hours (e.g., 7 AM–10 AM).  
- **Distance limits** (`<distance_limit>`): Trucks must finish their route within fuel constraints.  
- **Open routes**: Trucks end their shift at the final stop (e.g., a recycling center).  
*Goal*: Minimize total travel distance while ensuring all bins are serviced on time.
label: ovrpmbltw

title: Same-Day Retail Delivery with Returns Handling

- **Time windows** (`<time_windows>`): Stores accept returns/deliveries only during business hours.  
- **Duration limits** (`<distance_limit>`): Drivers work 8-hour shifts; routes must avoid overtime.  
- **Open routes**: Vans remain at the last store for overnight parking.  
*Goal*: Maximize daily served stores while minimizing fuel costs.
label: ovrpmbltw

title: Medical Lab Sample Collection and Supply Delivery

Units (capacity: `<capacity>`) must adhere to:

- **Distance limits** (`<distance_limit>`): Units cannot exceed 200 km/day due to refrigeration limits.  
- **Mixed backhauls**: A unit might deliver supplies to Clinic A, then collect samples from Clinic B.  
*Goal*: Ensure all clinics are served within constraints while minimizing fleet size.
